      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOME SECRET (1) flew the lids with a sensational early split and hit the frame with a 0.8 lengths second (17.09) over 300m at Healesville. The form out of last race has been strong. Can measure up this time. BRINDLE MOTION (2) boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten 1.2 lengths (25.20) behind Sunday Stroller at Sale. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from five attempts. Hard to beat again. DR. ZAIDEN (3) ran below his best last time finishing fifth (24.92) over 435m at Sale in a Mix 6/7. Solid winning record at this trip. Should be about the money. SIMBA ROSE (7) drops in trip and cannot be left out.",
